chunks.text: .................11 | | Knowledge Check ................................................................................................................11 | | Appendix A- Defer Work Business Process.............................................................................12 | User Guide Defer Work - HTM Admin THIS PAGE INTENTIONALLY LEFT BLANK. ## DEFER WORK ## Summary This lesson provides an overview of deferring a Preventive Maintenance (PM) Work Order, how to update a PM Result to deferred, and when to notify the Equipment Inventory Listing (EIL) Official. If a PM Work Order must be deferred, a PM Result of DEFER is recorded, and a value is added to describe the reason for deferral. Examples of reasons for deferral include: - · Asset could not be located - · Asset is out of service - · Asset is loaned out A deferred Work Order may be continued to completion if a missing Asset is found within the time frame in which the Work Order must be performed.

ed - · Asset is out of service - · Asset is loaned out A deferred Work Order may be continued to completion if a missing Asset is found within the time frame in which the Work Order must be performed. Otherwise, the Work Order will be closed with a PM result of deferred, with narrative describing the reason. For more information about this process, please go to Appendix A - Defer Work Business Process to view the flowchart and process narrative. ## User Roles and Responsibilities The audience for this training includes the following user roles: | Role | Responsibility | |-------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | FMAdmin | Receives, classifies and disposes building service equipment(BSE) Assets; reviewsand approvesWork Orders; creates PMs (preventive maintenance

---------------------------------------------| | FMAdmin | Receives, classifies and disposes building service equipment(BSE) Assets; reviewsand approvesWork Orders; creates PMs (preventive maintenance); approvesPM work deferrals; creates JobPlans | | FM Supervisor | Reviewsand evaluatesService Requests;plans and approves work;monitors and assigns Work Orders to FMTechs in their Responsible Shops. | | FMTech | Performswork and completes Work Orders; identifies needto deferwork; updatesPM work status | | FMWork OrderClerk | Reviewsand evaluatesService Requests;receives, classifies and disposes building service equipment (BSE) Assets; reviewsand evaluates Service Requests;plans and approves work and assigns Work Ordersto FMshops; creates PMs (preventive maintenance) | | HTM Admin | Classifies Assets;reviewsand approvesWork Orders; creates PMs (preventive maintenance); approvesPM work deferrals; creates Job Plans; determines needfor decontamination/sanitization of turned in Assets | | HTM

Examples of reasons for deferral include: - · Asset could not be located - · Asset is out of service - · Asset is loaned out NOTE: If the missing Asset is found within the window for finishing the Work Order, return to the Execute Work process. If the reason for the deferral does not change, the Tech may complete the Work Order and record a note explaining the circumstances. - Step 1. From the Start Center , select the appropriate Work Order from My Work Orders portlet. NOTE : You can sort columns in descending or ascending order by clicking the column heading. You may also use the filter fields to find the appropriate wor

NOTE : You can sort columns in descending or ascending order by clicking the column heading. You may also use the filter fields to find the appropriate work order or click the 'Next Page' link to move the next set of records. Figure 1. My Work Orders Portlet Step 2. The Work Order opens in the Work Order Tracking application on the Work Order tab. Figure 2. Work Order Tab Step 3. In the PM Result field, select the Select Value select the PM Result DEFER. (magnifying glass) icon and then Figure 3. PM Result Select Value - Defer Step 4. In the Deferred Reason field, select the Select Value (magnifying glass) icon and then select the appropriate Deferred Reason Code . Possible Deferred Reason Codes: - · CNL - Could Not Locate - · IU - In Use - · LO - Loaned Out - · OOS - Out of service - · OTHER - Other Figure 4. Deferred Reason Select Value Dialog Box NOTE: If the reason the Work Order was deferred is NOT listed in the options available (liste

- Loaned Out - · OOS - Out of service - · OTHER - Other Figure 4. Deferred Reason Select Value Dialog Box NOTE: If the reason the Work Order was deferred is NOT listed in the options available (listed above), type the appropriate reason in the Other Deferral Reason field, which is required before the Work Order can be saved . IMPORTANT! This code is used to track all PM Work Orders that are deferred for reasons other than the options available. ## Step 5. Select the Save icon on the toolbar. NOTE: The PM Result and Deferred Reason were added to the VA Work Order Detail Report. When the report is printed, the data is part of the historical record. ## NOTIFY EIL OFFICIAL IF WARRANTED Maximo offers the Admin or FM Supervisor the opportunity to send an e-mail notification to the EIL Official, which usually occurs when the Asset cannot be located. - · If the missing Asset is found within the window for finishing the Work Order, return to the Execute Work process.
